The paper deals with distributed computing models and their equivalence, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves topological reasoning, which is related to Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The use of modular structures and analysis techniques suggests a connection to Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with adversarial sub-models and schedulers, which is related to Systems and Control (cs.SY).
